parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause issues with the battery, starting system, and other electrical components.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the battery drains quickly
the vehicle won't start
the electrical system service required light comes on
the vehicle shakes while idling and then shuts off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch can cause the door to not lock or unlock properly, leading to safety issues while driving. It can also cause inconvenience and difficulty in entering or exiting the vehicle.
symptoms: The door latch will not lock or unlock with the fob or driver panel
the door can come open while driving
the door can be unlocked from the outside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.

the vehicle jerks when coming to a stop
the sensor does not go off
the vehicle rear-ends another vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of an accident, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag system service required light comes on and off constantly
the passenger seat gets wet and the light will go off when the seat dries (although the seat has never been wet).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition or starter can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and difficulty.
